Keeps my attention. Vibrant characters although Piper is the least appealing. Suspenseful with enough drama and romance to keep it engaging. The flashbacks are interesting and provide insight and depth into the characters present situation. The following things are covered: Poor choices, life circumstances, socio economic factors, fate, destiny, choice and debate of these topics. Power struggles, good vs bad, loyalties and survival. How much can people change or want to change? The laws of attraction. Injustice and ethical obligations. Family influence or lack there of, the cycles of mistakes. Racial dynamics, the questions of Friendship. Social ties and isolation.